- "sailing in the vast seas of Java knowledge" metaphorically refers to studying Java courses;
- "guides" and "lighthouses" metaphorically refer to instructors and departments;
- "sails" and "shipped titles" metaphorically refer to topics and course titles;
- "stars" metaphorically refers to students;
- "voyaged" metaphorically refers to resource access or usage;
- "depth of their voyage" metaphorically refers to the duration of their activity or engagement with the course resources.

sql:
SELECT c.course_title, t.topic_name
FROM courses c
LEFT JOIN topics t ON c.topic_id = t.topic_id;

